The paper deals with the undecidability of equality in a version of Martin-Lof type theory, which is a foundational topic in computer science and logic. The paper also discusses the free category with families and the free locally cartesian closed category, which are concepts related to category theory and programming language semantics. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science), cs.PL (Programming Languages), and cs.LOgic (Logic in Computer Science). Additionally, the paper also involves information theory (cs.IT) and category theory (cs.CC), which are relevant sub-categories.
